    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA281-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu vaṉpoṟai (ET: vaṉpuṟai) yetiraḻinta talaimakaḷ tōḻikkuc colliyatu.
            2. āṟṟāḷ eṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻi talaimakaṭku uraittūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what SHE who was desolate inspite of encouragement said to the confidante. 2. It is also what the confidante who was anxious that [she] would not bear it said to HER.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA281">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            māciṉ maratta paliyuṇ kākkai</l>
<l>            vaḷiporu neṭuñciṉait taḷiyoṭu tūṅki</l>
<l>            velpōrc cōḻar kaḻāark koḷḷu</l>
<l>            nalvakai mikupalik koṭaiyō ṭukukku</l>
<l>            maṭaṅkāc coṉṟi yampal yāṇar </l>
<l>            viṭakkuṭaip peruñcō ṟuḷḷuvaṉa viruppa</l>
<l>            maḻaimain tuṟṟa māliru ṇaṭunāṭ</l>
<l>            ṭānam muḻaiya rākavu nānam</l>
<l>            paṉikkaṭu maiyi ṉaṉiperi taḻuṅkit</l>
<l>            tuñcā mākalu maṟivō </l>
<l>            raṉpilar tōḻinaṅ kāta lōrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>He [is] devoid of love, friend, our lover,</l>
<l>he who knows we will be sleepless ,</l>
<l rend="indent">being very much troubled by the harshness of our [eyes’] dew,</l>
<l rend="indent2">even when<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ākavum</term>: here we seem to be facing a rhetorical problem: why would SHE be suffering at night when HE is near her − unless we asume that the situation is <term xml:lang="ta">varaivu kaṭāyatu</term>, with the implication that he will have to leave her again during this fearful night.</note> he himself [is] near us</l>
<l rend="indent3">at midnight in great darkness when rain came in a frenzy,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while the offering-eating crows of the flawless tree,</l>
<l rend="indent2">hanging with the drops on the long branches beaten by the wind,</l>
<l rend="indent2">are perched, remembering the great cooked rice with meat</l>
<l rend="indent3">from the nice many yields of endless boiled rice</l>
<l rend="indent3">that is shed along with the giving of much offering of good sort,</l>
<l rend="indent4">when the Cōḻar victorious in battle take Kaḻāar-ghat.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
